{
  "texts": [
    "While our initial goal was to investigate the performance of our PsychGenerator-trained classifier on external datasets, we identified several fundamental differences between Big Five Essay and PsychGenerator that complicate direct comparisons and may limit the interpretability of such experiments:",
    "• Big Five Essay: This dataset comprises essays written by individuals, often as part of psychological studies to assess personality traits.",
    "The content is typically reflective, introspective, and covers a wide range of personal experiences and thoughts.",
    "Its context length is usually lengthy, often exceeding several hundred words, as they are structured essays delving deep into personal narratives.",
    "• PsychGenerator: This dataset consists of social media posts, particularly from platforms like Facebook."
  ]
}